quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  31,1,"Alif Lām Mīm."
  31,2,"These are the signs of the Wise Scripture,"
  31,3,"a guidance and a mercy for those who excel in doing good:"
  31,4,"those who establish the prayer and bring1the purifying charity2and of the Hereafter they are certain."
  31,5,"Those are rightly guided by their Lord, and those are the successful."
  31,6,"And among mankind is one who trades in distracting tales to make(people) stray1 from the way of Allah without knowledge, and to take it2 for a mockery; for those is a demeaning punishment."
  31,7,"And when Our signs1are recited to him, he turns away arrogantly as though he did not hear them, as though there is deafness in his ears. So givesg him glad tidings2of a painful punishment."
  31,8,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds—for them are the Gardens of Bliss,"
  31,9,"abiding therein, a true promise of Allah. And He is the Almighty, the All-Wise."
  31,10,"He created the heavens without any pillars that youpl can see, and cast firm mountains into the earth lest it sway with you, and scattered throughout it all kinds of treading creatures. And from the sky We sent down water, and We germinated therein many noble kinds of plants."